OCTOBER 11-14, 2024

Austin, Texas, USA

Three days of connection, coherence, and fun at a classic American summer camp for founders, builders, and leaders of the network society ecosystem

Follow @tnsdotcamp for updates

Questions? Email team@tns.camp

Why

Every movement begins with a group of people aligned around a shared vision of something betterto cohere around relationships and values before tech platforms and economic models. The network before the state.

This event is calling together an intimate, curated group of leaders that represent a diverse array of perspectives for three days of facilitated workshops, unconference-style talks, and the magic that comes from late-night fireside conversations.

Network Society Camp will be taking place at a classic American summer camp to shake up the conference-as-usual vibes and remind us that work and play enhance each other.

What

Network Society Camp will take place from October 11-14 near Austin, Texas, USA.

The venue is 90 minutes outside of Austin, and we will have shuttles running to and from AUS airport for attendees. We will provide housing, meals, and activities so you can focus on making new connections and deepening old ones. Tickets to TNS Camp are $700, which is all-inclusive onsite (covers attendance, lodging, food, drinks, and buses for the whole event). We offer discounts and scholarships to those who need them.

Interested in deepening relationships with fellow network buildersboth fans and skeptics of network societies? We're curating participants via a mix of public applications and direct invites. This event will be an intimate gathering with a curated set of attendees. Applications will be accepted on a rolling basis, with a registration cutoff of September 27th.

FAQ

What do you suggest I put on my packing list?

It's gonna be mostly hot and sunny, but temperatures drop in the evenings so dress appropriately. The forecast is 90s during the day and 60s at night. Here are some things we recommend:

  • clothes
  • swimsuit
  • comfortable shoes
  • flip flops for showers
  • sunglasses
  • hat
  • sunscreen
  • pants and a longsleeve for the evenings
  • towel
  • toiletries
  • bug spray
  • tech basics (charger, powerbank)
  • earplugs and eyemask for sleeping
  • something delightful to share with other attendees

What are sleeping conditions like?

This is a children's summer camp and as such you'll be on twin XL bunks in shared, rustic rooms. There are hotels in the area as an option for people who don't feel comfortable with the cabins, but we strongly encourage you to sleep on site for the full, shared experience.

What are we doing at Camp?

  • Connecting with people from around the world passionate about the movement.
  • Diving deep in facilitated small group conversations about network state theory and practice.
  • Learning from the field through participant-led conversations and workshops.
  • Enjoying fun and games unique to summer camp (Archery! Canoes! Campfire! Cocktails!).

What about network cities, network states, network sovereignties, coordi-nations, network nations, and other adjacent ideas?

We've called this event Network Society Camp because it aims to include all of these ideas. This movement is inherently pluralistic, and a core goal of the event is to bring together people with a wide range of perspectives and approaches. If you are interested in any of these ideas, your perspective will be an important part of the collective sensemaking we will do together.

Can I bring my children?

Yes, this event is at a summer camp and will be great for all ages. Kids tickets are free! We are specifically designing it to be family friendly, so please get in touch if you want to bring your family so we can work with you.
